args.natural_language_statement: Show that SL(n) ⊲ GL(n) and that GL(n)/SL(n) ≅ R^×, where SL(n) is the special linear group of n×n real matrices of determinant 1, GL(n) is the general linear group of invertible n×n real matrices, and R^× is the multiplicative group of nonzero real numbers. Translate into Lean4 (no proof) and end the statement with := by sorry.

retrieved_examples.nl: The determinant map induces a group homomorphism det : GL(n,R) → R^× whose kernel is SL(n,R), hence SL(n,R) ⊲ GL(n,R) and GL(n,R)/SL(n,R) ≅ R^×.
retrieved_examples.lean:
variable {R : Type*} [Field R] {n : Type*} [Fintype n] [DecidableEq n]

open Matrix

noncomputable def det_hom : Units (Matrix n n R) →* Rˣ :=
  Units.map (det : Matrix n n R →* R)

theorem SL_normal : ( { A : Units (Matrix n n R) // (A : Matrix n n R).det = 1 } : Set (Units (Matrix n n R))).IsNormal :=
  := by sorry
